USAGE="Usage: ${bold}pkg merge PKGNAME,PKGNAME,.. [--with-deps] [--split]${endcolour}

Merge multiple packages into a single package. The newly
created package file will a .PET.

If ${bold}--with-deps${endcolour} is given, the dependencies of each listed
package will also be merged into the final package file.

If ${bold}--split${endcolour} is given, the newly generated packages will
then be split into separate EXE, DEV, DOC and NLS packages.

PKGNAME(s) must be ${bold}comma separated (no spaces)${endcolour}!
"
